definitions.definition: the twenty-sixth letter of the alphabet.
denoting the next after Y in a set of items, categories, etc.
denoting a third unknown or unspecified person or thing.
examples: X sold a car to Y (a car dealer) who in turn sold it to Z (a finance company)

definitions.definition: the third unknown quantity in an algebraic expression.
denoting the third axis in a three-dimensional system of coordinates.
a shape like that of a capital Z.
examples: the same old Z-shaped crack in the paving stone

definitions.definition: used in repeated form to represent the sound of buzzing or snoring.
examples: I'm being overcome with weariness as I write … zzzzz, zzzzz

definitions.definition: the number of protons in the nucleus of an atom, which determines the chemical properties of an element and its place in the periodic table.
